prompt:
Give me tailwind code to create the play + reset buttons at the bottom left. You can do
import { FaPlay, FaStepBackward } from 'react-icons/fa'; 
to get the icons

generation:
Here's the Tailwind CSS code to create those media control buttons:

```jsx
import { FaPlay, FaStepBackward } from 'react-icons/fa';

const MediaControls = () => {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <button className="p-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">
        <FaStepBackward className="w-4 h-4" />
      </button>
      <button className="p-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors">
        <FaPlay className="w-4 h-4" />
      </button>
    </div>
  );
};
```

This will create buttons that:
- Are arranged horizontally with a small gap between them
- Have padding around the icons
- Start with a gray color and turn white on hover
- Have a smooth color transition effect
- Use appropriately sized icons

If you want to make the buttons more interactive, you can add active states:

```jsx
<button className="p-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-white active:text-gray-500 transition-colors">
```

And if you want to match the dark background from the image:

```jsx
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 bg-gray-900 p-4">
```

The actual button click handlers can be added like this:

```jsx
const MediaControls = () => {
  const handlePlay = () => {
    // Play logic here
  };

  const handleReset = () => {
    // Reset logic here
  };

  return (
    <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
      <button 
        onClick={handleReset}
        className="p-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors"
      >
        <FaStepBackward className="w-4 h-4" />
      </button>
      <button 
        onClick={handlePlay}
        className="p-2 text-gray-400 hover:text-white transition-colors"
      >
        <FaPlay className="w-4 h-4" />
      </button>
    </div>
  );
};
```
